.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-migrate-kdf - Migrate vault KDF from scrypt to argon2id


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira migrate kdf [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Migrate the vault's key derivation function from scrypt to argon2id.

.PP
⚠️  This command is a STUB and not yet implemented.
A future release will provide the full migration workflow.

.PP
Argon2id is the industry standard for password hashing (2025+) and provides
stronger resistance against GPU-based attacks compared to scrypt.

.PP
In the meantime:
  1. Back up your vault: cp -r ~/.openpass ~/.openpass.backup
  2. Wait for a future release with full migration support
  3. Run 'openpass doctor' to track the migration recommendation


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for kdf


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  openpass migrate kdf
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-migrate(1)\fP
